      <body>Technically, is no such thing as &quot;production&quot; mode to Rails. Your environment is determined by the behavior you setup in the environment config. We don't do any ENV == &quot;production&quot; in the framework. cache_classes is the default for the production template that is generated for you.</body>
      <body-html>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;
Technically, is no such thing as &quot;production&quot; mode to Rails. Your environment is determined by the behavior you setup in the environment config. We don't do any ENV == &quot;production&quot; in the framework. cache_classes is the default for the production template that is generated for you.
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</body-html>
